{
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionVirtual Reality (VR) technology emerged in the 1950s and its early rudimentary experiences have evolved into what is known today as Immersive Virtual Reality (iVR) [1].",
    "Since then, iVR technology has undergone significant development, and is a relevant discipline for society [2].",
    "Early VR technology was primarily restricted to military and research activities [3].",
    "However, new uses for VR emerged over the years, such as education and training [4], as well as the dissemination of Cultural Heritage (CH).",
    "Combinations of CH with VR technology began to be explored at around the 1990s [5]."
  ]
}